_:B50cb7a0ca1632e0f5941e2e553c3b99d <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#annotatedTarget> "A muscle organ that consists of skeletal muscle tissue ensheathed in epimysium, that develops from myotome and that is innervated by some somatic motor neuron. Skeletal muscles are typically attached (via a tendon) to a bone but there are exceptions (e.g. intrinsic tongue muscles)." .
